title: Bluebridge ferry has left Welington for good
text:
Bluebridge ferry has left Welington for good TOM HUNT Last updated 09:24, September 1 2015 FAIRFAX NZ 
Bluebridge ferry Santa Regina has left Wellington for good. 
Bluebridge's first Cook Strait passenger ferry has left Wellington for the last time. 
The Santa Regina, which has run between Wellington and Picton since 2002, sailed from Wellington on Monday, spokeswoman Wendy Pannett said. 
She was on her way to Auckland and would be put up for sale. 
"She has been a much-loved vessel. Not only by staff and crew but also the travelling public. 
"It was very sad to see her go." 
Santa Regina was Bluebridge's first passenger ship when Strait Shipping started carrying passengers as well as freight in 2002. 
Her last sailing was on June 20 and she had been tied up since then.
